The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Lanka gunbattle 

 Colombo, Sept. 17 (Reuters): Sri Lankan army and Tamil Tiger rebels exchanged fire and skirmished at sea today, after a four-day lull in fighting around the Jaffna peninsula. 

 A military source said Sri Lankan naval vessels and Sea Tigers of the LTTE also clashed at sea and that one rebel boat had been sunk. 

 Hamas talks 

 Ramallah, West Bank (Reuters): Mahmoud Abbass office on Sunday said the Palestine President has frozen talks with the ruling Hamas movement to form a coalition government after the rebel group said it would not accept an interim peace deal with Israel. Both the sides have accused each other of trying to derail the planned government. 

 Pak scientist 

 Karachi (AP): Former Pakistani scientist Abdul Qadeer Khan, who has confessed to leaking nuclear weapons technology to North Korea, Iran and Libya, was discharged on Sunday from a hospital after undergoing a surgery. Khan, 70, had surgery last week for prostate cancer. 

 Ershad case 

 Dhaka (Reuters): A Bangladesh court has cleared former military ruler Hossain Mohammad Ershad of graft charges in a land allotment case. Ershad seized power in a coup in 1982 when he was the army chief. 




